    <!-- ON-PAGE ANCHOR TARGET -->
    <section id="techniques" class="anchor-target">
      <p class="section-label">The Playbook</p>
      <h2>Core Pass Rush Techniques</h2>
      <p>Every move in a pass rusher's arsenal has a counter — and a counter to that counter. The best rushers chain two or three together.</p>

      <!-- ORDERED LIST WITH EMBEDDED UNORDERED LISTS (required element) -->
      <ol class="moves-list">
        <li>
          Speed / Contain Moves
          <ul>
            <li>Speed rush — flat path around the tackle using speed-to-power conversion</li>
            <li>Ghost / dip — bending the edge with a flattened back angle</li>
            <li>Spin move — 360° rotation off a planted foot to beat an over-set tackle</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          Power Moves
          <ul>
            <li>Bull rush — drive the blocker backward into the pocket using leverage and leg drive</li>
            <li>Push-pull — set up with a push to create extension, then yank the blocker past</li>
            <li>Long stick — initial punch to the chest to control the blocker's hands</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          Hand Fighting Techniques
          <ul>
            <li>Swipe — knock the blocker's inside hand away to break the grip</li>
            <li>Rip — underhand move driving under the blocker's arm</li>
            <li>Swim — overhand move over the blocker's arm to clear the shoulder</li>
            <li>Chop — attacking the blocker's hands at the wrists before contact</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          Counter Moves
          <ul>
            <li>Inside counter (hump / spin inside) — after selling the edge</li>
            <li>Chop-and-go — stun the hands then convert to a speed rush</li>
            <li>Club-and-rip — club the outside arm then rip underneath</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          Situational Awareness
          <ul>
            <li>Reading set tendencies — kick slide vs. vertical set vs. slide protection</li>
            <li>Recognizing screen and draw calls from the blocker's body language</li>
            <li>Working in tandem — coordinating stunts and loops with an interior rusher</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

